Tottenham Hotspur’s squad to face Pep Guardiola’s Manchester City in the Premier League on Saturday evening has been revealed. According to Football London, Tottenham manager, Jose Mourinho, has released a full squad of 27 players to tackle Man City. Mourinho had already confirmed during his pre-match press conference on Friday that the likes of Harry Winks, Davinson Sanchez and Gedson Fernandes are all doubts for the Man City clash, while Erik Lamela remains out. Mourinho’s men head to the game following a 1-0 victory over West Brom in their last Premier League clash before the international break. Tottenham’s full squad to face Man City: Goalkeepers: Hugo Lloris, Joe Hart, Paulo Gazzaniga. Defenders: Toby Alderweireld, Davinson Sanchez, Serge Aurier, Ben Davies, Japhet Tanganga, Dennis Cirkin, Sergio Reguilon, Joe Rodon. Midfielders: Harry Winks, Eric Dier, Moussa Sissoko, Dele Alli, Tanguy Ndombele, Gedson Fernandes, Jack Clarke, Pierre-Emile Hojbjerg, Harvey White, Giovani Lo Celso. Forwards: Lucas Moura, Son Heung-min, Harry Kane, Steven Bergwijn, Gareth Bale, Carlos Vinicius. The kick-off time for the match is 6:30 pm.